data.title: Baldwin Wallace Athletics
data.text:
BALDWIN WALLACE ATHLETICS INFORMATION: Kayla Harris will be entering her fourth and final season of volleyball at Baldwin Wallace University in 2013-2014. She has earned her third varsity letter.

ACADEMIC HONORS: In 2012-2013, Kalya was inducted into the Chi Alpha Sigma Athletics Honor Society.

GENERAL VOLLEYBALL INFORMATION: Kayla has started off to a solid volleyball career thus far. B-W has recorded a 38-26 overall record during her first two seasons as a Yellow Jacket. She has appeared in 17 games played and has recorded 12 kills and five total blocks.

As a freshman in 2010, Kayla played in her first season of volleyball. She played in fourteen games and recorded 7 kills, 2 set assists, and 3 digs for the Yellow Jackets as the middle hitter.

As a sophomore in 2011, Kayla played in her second season of volleyball. Kayla played in three total games as she recorded 5 kills, and 5 total blocks.

As a junior in 2012-13, Kayla played in her third season of volleyball. Kayla played in a total of 67 games as she recorded 147 kills and 451 total attacks.

As a senior in 2013-2014, Kayla will play in her fourht season of volleyball and look to earn her fourth varsity letter.

HIGH SCHOOL INFORMATION:

HIGH SCHOOL ATTENDED: Lima

NAME OF HIGH SCHOOL CONFERENCE: Greater Buckeye
